node.text:
Today is World Day Against Trafficking in Persons, and I wanted to highlight the incredible work that my friend @timballard89 and his amazing organization @ourrescue are doing…

Tim has dedicated his life to freeing children all over the world from lives of slavery. That’s where his mission led him to begin O.U.R, and I’m so thankful that we were able to connect a few years ago…

We had the incredible opportunity to help produce their documentary “Operation Toussaint” that has helped show the amazing work they’re doing every day shining a very bright light in the darkest parts of the world. The work that Tim and his team are doing is SO important, and I’m honored and grateful to do whatever possible to help in their mission. 

Head to their profile at @ourrescue to see how you can #RiseUp and help #EndHumanTrafficking!!!

node.title: Are you ready to #RiseUp for children?!?

node.text: As an entrepreneur, do you struggle going on vacations..? If so, this message is for you! I made this video a few years ago, but thought it was appropriate to post, now that we’re half way through the summer… in hopes to remind you that you’re not weird… you’re an Entrepreneur, and that’s ok!!

The last 12 months have been hard for many…

But for those who were at FHL, we were prepared… One month before the lockdown, we had 5,000 ‘Funnel Hackers’ together at FHL, and @TonyRobbins predicted what was about to happen…

We just released an “After Movie” from FHL 2020, and it INSTANTLY gets me back in state to continue to create… to work… to serve!!! I can only hope it does the same for you :)

node.text:
The hardest step to take is the first one… then each after that becomes a little easier :)   

Leading into our FHL event week, this has been on my mind a lot... I know it’s hard to get started, finding that initial momentum can be tough. But I want you to know that once you start, things slowly fall into place, along as you keep pushing forward…

So stop waiting, because your people need you and they need to hear your message. I promise the initial push will be so worth it in the end :)

node.text:
Life should be filled with things that interest you, that excites you… but it’s up to you to find the spark that ignites your fire :)

And that’s truly what this journey and any journey is about! Finding the spark that ignites the fire in you. The one thing that interests you that you could spend days geeking out on…

The key is to find that passion, find that spark, and immerse yourself in it …and that’s how you’re going to turn your spark into a fire ;)

So I'm curious, what is your spark?!?

It’s okay to not have everything figured out!!! The only thing that matters is that you keep trying :)

I want you to realize that no one starts their journey out successful… it takes years if not decades to get things figured out, and that’s okay!!!  

Great things take time. Give me a “🙌” if you’re with me on this!

node.text:
Not everyone is going to agree with the decisions you make…

Prepare to offend some people, upset some people, and even lose some people along the way to make the decisions you need to in order to grow!!!  

It may not be easy to accept, but you're not going to have the support or belief from everyone in your life... but that shouldn’t affect you from moving forward!!! Have faith in yourself and in every decision you make with confidence, and the people that stick around will be those worth keeping :)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Russell Brunson on September 11, 2021. May be an image of ball.

node.text:
What happens when you take away freedom from the Prime Movers… (AKA entrepreneurs) 

For anyone wondering how this plays out, read Atlas Shrugged. When the government comes in and takes away freedoms and make it so the prime movers don’t want to produce anymore… well, the ending isn’t good for anyone. 

These are 3 statues that I had commissions that will be standing in my office soon.  The first represents Atlas (my entrepreneurs) holding the weight of the world in their shoulders… 

This is a responsibility we happily bare. 

The second statue is Atlas shrugging… and the third is him walking away from it all. 

We are quickly seeing the government over stepping their reach and taking away our freedoms. 

I don’t get political EVER online. I don’t care if you’re on the left or the right.  I don’t care if you got a jab or not. As long as your choices don’t effect my ability to produce, I am fine letting you do you. 

As  Voltaire said: "I may disagree with what you have to say, but I will defend, to the death, your right to say it."

But… when you try to take away my freedoms… this effects everything. 

For the record, I won’t take away my employees freedoms. If it means I have to pay fines to protect them, I will.  If it gets worse, perhaps that will be the point that I shrug, and walk away. 

I hope not. I love what I do. I love producing. I love my life. Our estimates right now show that ClickFunnels has conservatively created close to a million jobs and counting. 

When the entrepreneurs start to shrug, and walk way, we are all in trouble.  Fight for everyone’s rights, even if you disagree with what they want to do with those rights.

May be a Twitter screenshot of 2 people and text that says 'Russell Brunson @russellbrunson 208-231-3797 000 Successful people plan for 3 generations. Unsuccessful people plan for Friday night. What are you planning for?'.

node.text:
What we give our time and attention impacts everything...

Those that are truly successful aren’t just concerned about what’s going on this weekend…they’re planning on how to win in the future ;)

So are you focused on the future, or are you focused on Friday night?

Now let me be clear, there’s nothing wrong with enjoying down time…but it’s hard to create a lasting impact if that’s the only thing you’re living for!!! It all comes down to what you’re truly focused on…

Let me know if you’re with me on this!!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Russell Brunson on September 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ruu Russell Brunson @russellbrunson 208-231-3797 000 Graduate college with $100,000 debt, people cheer for you. Get married & spend $20,000 for one day, people cheer for you. Take a $200,000 loan from the bank to buy your 1st house, people cheer for you. (SW pe left)'.

node.text:
Don’t get lost in what other people think are the only “correct” things to invest in…

This isn’t to say investing in education, your marriage, or housing is a BAD thing…but when the same people that cheer these things on try to sway you from investing in your life missions and goals…it’s time to reevaluate.

If you’ve been wanting to start your journey, NOW is the time to do it! Stop letting the opinions of others determine what you do!!!

Some will say it’s a good idea, some will say it’s risky… but the only thing that matters is that YOU believe in the mission you’re on and that you take that first step forward and never stop investing in yourself…

So, who’s with me?!?
